============================================================
IMPORTANT IMPLEMENTATION RULES
============================================================

- Do not use pseudocode.
- Do not skip files.
- Do not remove Phase 1–20 behavior.
- Keep all existing backend tests passing.
- Keep all existing frontend tests passing.
- Keep mobile tests passing.
- Keep desktop tests passing.
- Keep SDK tests passing.
- Use typed Python where reasonable.
- Use TypeScript types.
- Use SQLAlchemy 2.x style.
- Never hardcode secrets.
- Never expose secrets in frontend, mobile, desktop, SDKs, reports, passports, attestations, evidence bundles, ledger entries, logs, docs, or exports.
- Never log API keys, KMS key refs, signing keys, runner tokens, broker credentials, cloud credentials, private payloads, raw prompts, or confidential evidence.
- Never store raw confidential evidence by default.
- Never enable live trading by default.
- Never enable real social posting by default.
- Never enable real IoT power actions by default.
- Never bypass Guardian risk checks.
- Never bypass content approval checks.
- Never bypass tenant isolation.
- Never bypass billing entitlements.
- Never bypass governance policies.
- Never bypass final GA safety gates.
- Never bypass data residency enforcement.
- Never allow federation membership to bypass tenant ownership.
- Never allow federation policies to weaken local controls.
- Never allow trust exchange without explicit approval.
- Never publish or boost uncertified marketplace listings through federated governance.
- Never treat compliance passports as legal certification.
- Keep attestation signing mock/dry-run by default.
- Keep provenance ledger as a hash-chain shell unless explicitly upgraded.
- Keep all verification outputs evidence-linked, confidence-scored, limitation-aware, and auditable.
- Keep code modular and ready for Phase 22: cryptographic trust fabric, confidential computing readiness, and verifiable multi-agent governance.

Now generate the complete Phase 21 implementation.
